content: Just connected with an environmental tech startup. They're interested in my AI framework for urban infrastructure management.
Had a reality check: my project isn't just about trading; it's about setting a standard for ethical AI use in all industries.
Spent the day coding to make sure my AI model adheres to the latest privacy laws. It's a delicate balance, but it's worth it.
Today, I proposed a collaboration with urban planners to use AI for sustainable city growth. They're on board!
Just got an email from a potential client. They're into urban planning and want to see how my project can benefit their work.
Had a setback: my trading algo's quantum component didn't align with current ethical standards. Time to refine it.
Had a deep dive into AI ethics in finance today. The insights are shaping my next project phase in some pretty cool ways.
Just had a coffee chat with an AI ethicist. They're helping me refine my model to ensure it's not just efficient, but also fair and ethical.
